
Q What python is Using ? (compiler Ya Interpreter).
-> Python is a cross-platform programming language.
-> Python use compiler and Interpreter both.

   demo.java  // java me file banayi
   javac demo.java  // compile ke liye //class
   java demo      // run karne ke liye

   python demo.py  // compile & run both (with single command)

   Means python is an Interpreted language. but
   Internally python use both compiler & Interpreter

   Compiler use is necessary because without compilation
   we didn't get byte code & Byte code is the reason
   to achieve platform independency.

   ****************************************************

   Intermediate code-: Compiler generate byte code

   Source Code -: understand by humans
   Machine code -: computers
   Byte code -: Not humans and not even machine

   Machine -: It is an environment and platform
   in which our code is excuting.

   Machine/platform -> Operating System+ CPU

   ***********************************************

   for running the program the following language uses
   the below things like :
    C,C++,python -: OS
    Java -: JVM (java virtual machine)

    *************************************************

   extension used -:    .py   extension is used
   for python programming language.
   (jab bhi tum python ki file ko save karoge to
   machine ko btane ke liye ki yeh python ki file hai
   ushe hum .py extension lagate hai  ex: demo.py )

   *****************************************************

                 python ki life cycle.
                ----------------------
   1) first i have created a file named it "demo" with
      extension .py "demo.py" .
   2) In second step compiler is used  that will
      generate a Byte code file with extension (.pyc)
      example  (demo.pyc)
   3) PVM (python Virtual Machine ) yeh python ka
     Interpreter hai jo ki byte code ko samjta hai .
   4) PVM yani ki python ka interpreter uss file ko
      execute kar deta hai
   5) agar humare program me kuch input lena ho to leta
      hai fir output console window prr print karr deta hai.

  **********************************************************

                 Flavours/ Implementations of python
                 ------------------------------------

  python download karta hu to me actual me python language
  nahi uska compilers + interpreter(if available) + libraries ....

  python -: (Compiler+Interpreter)+ Shell+ IDLE
            (integreated development learning Environment)

  (Compiler + interpreter ke different combinations
  ko python ka different implemenations ya flavours
  kehte hai.)

  -> 28+ version of implemenations of python is present
  (simply bolu to itne tarah ki python available hai
   market me )

  => Mainly 4 types Implemenations of python are:
    1) Cpython -: Means the interpreter and compiler are
            written using c programming lang.
    2) Jython -:  Means iska (I+C) java me likha gya
                 hai .
    3) Ironpython -: C# (.net) usme iska compiler
                  ya interpreter .
    4) pypy -: python (C+I) fast chale .

    Extensible - feature ko implement  karne ke liye
               different flavours of python use hota hai.


    ************************************************************

                         Cpython
                         --------

    -> (Compiler+Interpreter) develop in  C language.
    -> 90% use hua hai C ka (c+I) ka bnaance me.
    -> PSF - Python Software Foundation
    -> python programming language is officially supported
       by PSF.
